OL,3,C'They've overlooked my child's death':
OL,4,CWrongful prosecutions in legal
OL,5,Cprocedure
OL,7,FAnd nearly one in three (58%) would
OL,8,Flikely have resulted in a different
OL,9,Foutcome if the defendant had access to
OL,10,Fa lawyer in open court.
OL,12,FIn one case we examined, a pensioner
OL,13,Fwas prosecuted for not paying his TV
OL,14,FLicence, despite explaining in the SJP
OL,15,Fform he returned that he had been in
OL,16,Fhospital undergoing heart surgery. He
OL,17,Fwas still convicted.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/26
