OL,3,C'They've overlooked my child's death':
OL,4,CWrongful prosecutions in legal
OL,5,Cprocedure
OL,7,F"This is the most extreme, horrible
OL,8,Fthing that's happened in my life, and
OL,9,FI would absolutely think that's a
OL,10,Fmitigating circumstance."
OL,12,FCases like this are being ruled on by
OL,13,Fmagistrates who are volunteers.
OL,15,FWe showed the findings of our
OL,16,Finvestigation to the Magistrates'
OL,17,FAssociation, and they admit mistakes
OL,18,Fare happening, they say, because
OL,19,Fprosecutors don't even read the
OL,20,Fexplanations from the people they're
OL,21,Ftrying to convict.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/26
