OL,3,C'They've overlooked my child's death':
OL,4,CWrongful prosecutions in legal
OL,5,Cprocedure
OL,7,F"There isn't that process of the
OL,8,Fprosecuting authority deciding if it
OL,9,Fpasses the 'public interest test'
OL,10,Fbased on what has been written by the
OL,11,Fdefendant, and that should happen,"
OL,12,FTom Franklin, the chief executive of
OL,13,Fthe Magistrates Association, said.
OL,15,FThe Magistrates' Association has set
OL,16,Fout 12 steps for reform to the SJP -
OL,17,Fthe main one being that prosecution
OL,18,Fauthorities must first read the
OL,19,Fexplanations being written by the
OL,20,Fdefendant before deciding if they want
OL,21,Fto proceed with the case at all.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/26
