OL,3,C'They've overlooked my child's death':
OL,4,CWrongful prosecutions in legal
OL,5,Cprocedure
OL,7,FMr Franklin said the response from the
OL,8,Fgovernment so far has been "muted".
OL,10,FThe absence of a review from the
OL,11,Fprosecuting authorities means if a
OL,12,Fdefendant ticks the guilty box and
OL,13,Fthen attempts to explain their
OL,14,F"mitigating circumstances", the
OL,15,Fmagistrate cannot undo the guilty
OL,16,Fplea. In effect, their fate has
OL,17,Falready been sealed.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/26
