OL,3,C'They've overlooked my child's death':
OL,4,CWrongful prosecutions in legal
OL,5,Cprocedure
OL,7,FIn such a case, the magistrate can
OL,8,Fonly take those mitigating
OL,9,Fcircumstances into consideration for a
OL,10,Fmore lenient punishment, but a
OL,11,Fconviction is a foregone conclusion.
OL,13,FTristan Kirk at the Evening Standard
OL,14,Fhas been investigating the SJP for the
OL,15,Flast four years.
OL,17,FHe has uncovered evidence of the
OL,18,Fsystem wrongfully convicting children,
OL,19,Fand he thinks it's because speed is
OL,20,Fbeing prioritised over justice.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/26
