OL,3,C'They've overlooked my child's death':
OL,4,CWrongful prosecutions in legal
OL,5,Cprocedure
OL,7,FThis isn't a story of lives being
OL,8,Fruined as a result of mistakes in the
OL,9,Fsystem, akin to the Post Office
OL,10,FHorizon IT scandal.
OL,12,FUnder the SJP, the punishment is often
OL,13,Fa relatively small fine, but to those
OL,14,Fwho have been convicted, the indignity
OL,15,Fof it all still matters.
OL,17,FWhat is similar to what happened with
OL,18,Fthe Post Office, however, is that
OL,19,Funder the SJP the power to prosecute
OL,20,Fhas been bestowed upon organisations.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/26
