OL,3,C'They've overlooked my child's death':
OL,4,CWrongful prosecutions in legal
OL,5,Cprocedure
OL,7,F"Once progressed to SJP, any defendant
OL,8,Fcan request a hearing in open court,
OL,9,Fbut those pleading guilty via SJP,
OL,10,Fincluding those with mitigating
OL,11,Faction, are considered by a
OL,12,Fmagistrate. These can be referred back
OL,13,Fto DVLA but whether or not to do so is
OL,14,Fa decision taken by the magistrate."
OL,16,FWith regard to the prosecution of a
OL,17,Fdeceased person, the DVLA told us they
OL,18,Frely on the family or the executor to
OL,19,Fnotify them that the registered keeper
OL,20,Fof a vehicle has passed away.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G21/26
